Life in the Matatiele, Mvenyane and Mount Frere communities will never be the same again given the massive development that is coming their way in the form of a R127 million road construction project.Eastern Cape Premier, Phumulo Masualle, who was joined by Eastern Cape MEC for Public Works, Thandiswa Marawu, on Thursday handed over the construction site of a 56 kilometre-long road between Matatiele and Mount Frere.A 100% black-owned company, Xesibe Constructions, won the tender to construct the road.The first phase of the road - a 14km stretch, is estimated to take 18 months to complete.Masualle sai that the road project was as a result of government working to improve the lives of residents.He also used the opportunity to condemn the abuse of women and children. 